INSERT INTO `modx_site_content` VALUES ('201','document','text/html','RASFULDI, Renaldo, Naldi','RASFULDI, Renaldo, Naldi','','1','','1','0','0','200','0','','<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"9\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"300\" src=\"content/images/campuslife/2014/image_cl_2014_mec_renaldo.jpg\" /></td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 120%;\"><img width=\"32\" height=\"32\" src=\"content/images/flag/ID.png\" /> Indonesia<br /></span></td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"bottom\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 140%;\">RASFULDI, Renaldo, Naldi<br /></span></strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"top\"><span style=\"font-size: 120%;\">Mechanical Engineering</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>I did my masters under the guidance of Professor Atsushi Tsutsumi. My research topic was &ldquo;Thermoelectric Heat Circulator Based on Self-Heat Recuperation Technology&rdquo;. It was a fundamental research in the field of chemical processing which when applied can significantly reduce the energy requirements of any chemical processes. My research involved both simulation and experimental work that was very satisfying for me personally since I was able to apply the simulations that I&rsquo;ve done immediately in the research lab. My research went as well as it did thanks to the guidance of Prof. Tsutsumi and the non-stop advice I received from my senpais during my study there.<br />When I first applied to the MEM program I couldn&rsquo;t speak any Japanese which was intimidating at first, but after receiving a few email replies from Umeda-san and Minegishi-san of the MEM office I felt assured that I could finish my application and contact prospective professors even with minimum knowledge of the Japanese language. <br />It didn&rsquo;t take me long to adapt to Todai and Japanese life. With the energetic Todai campus life in the hustling and bustling city of Tokyo, I believe many of the MEM students felt the same way I did. In fact, I enjoyed it so much that I decided to work in Tokyo after I graduated!</p>','1','5','1','1','0','1','1516172731','1','1516694243','0','0','0','1516694243','1','RASFULDI, Renaldo, Naldi','0','0','0','0','0','0','1');
INSERT INTO `modx_site_content` VALUES ('203','document','text/html','Lin Xiaojie','Lin Xiaojie','','1','','1','0','0','202','0','','<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"8\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"300\" src=\"content/images/campuslife/2014/image_cl_2014_mat_lin.jpg\" />&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img width=\"32\" height=\"32\" src=\"content/images/flag/CN.png\" /><span style=\"font-size: 120%;\"> China</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 140%;\"><strong>Lin Xiaojie</strong></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 120%;\">Materials Engineering</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Hi everyone, I am Xiaojie Lin, currently working as a Research Associate at the Department of Chemical Engineering, University of Washington, Seattle. I received my M.S degree (2011) and Ph.D degree (2014) in Materials Engineering from The University of Tokyo (UT) in Japan under the guidance of Prof. Kazuhiko Ishihara. I continued my research as Specialist for Academic Affairs in UT until Mar. 2016. <br />IME program in UT provides international student a platform for discovering new culture, exploring novel technology and making friends from all over the world. I really enjoy the study in UT and benefit a lot through IME program. Staff in IME program always kindly help students as much as they can. They arrange various parties and study tours each year to give us many opportunities for learning Japanese culture. Faculties in IME program are also top professional in Japan. I would also appreciate my supervisor and friends in UT for their kind encouragement and guidance. Studying in UT through IME program is a very memorable and valuable experience in my life.<br />Advocate excellence, pursue superexcellence, transcend ourselves. In IME program, you will have a variety of learning perspectives from international talents. I strongly recommend that you apply for this program and take advantage of honors and advanced courses offered at this top public university in Japan.</p>','1','5','1','1','0','1','1516692757','1','1516694965','0','0','0','1516692757','1','Lin Xiaojie','0','0','0','0','0','0','1');
INSERT INTO `modx_site_content` VALUES ('204','document','text/html','Feng Bin','Feng Bin','','2','','1','0','0','202','0','','<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\"8\"><img width=\"225\" height=\"300\" src=\"content/images/campuslife/2014/image_cl_2014_mat_feng.jpg\" /></td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><img width=\"32\" height=\"32\" src=\"content/images/flag/CN.png\" /> <span style=\"font-size: 120%;\">China</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 140%;\"><strong>Feng Bin</strong></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 120%;\">Materials Engineering</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The University of Tokyo is one of the best research institutes in the world, where I really enjoyed my research on materials science with the-state-of-the-art electron microscopies. In addition, Tokyo is a fascinating city with friendly people, multiple cultures and delicious food. IME program bridges the gap between non-Japanese speaking international students and complicated graduate school enrollment system in Japan. Thanks to this program, all the application process and courses are in English. The stuffs are really kindhearted, offering many supports to every foreign students for their lives in Japan. IME program also provides many unique activities to learn Japanese and Japanese cultures, where I also met a lot of international friends from different departments. So I strongly recommend all prospective students to join us, and without any doubt, IME program would be the best choice for you.</p>','1','5','2','1','0','1','1516694230','1','1516694945','0','0','0','1516694230','1','Feng Bin','0','0','0','0','0','0','1');
